notesStmt.note: Collective title taken from the caption title for the first and main work (p. 1).
Date based on the latest date for the main work (p. 482, 494); latest date for the additional works is 1731 (p. 653).

msContents.summary: Treatise on the 83 articles of Pierre Pithou's liberties of the Gallican church, which delineated the partial independence of the Catholic Church in France from the Pope, followed by additional notes on some of the articles, a collection of extracts from the writings of various popes compiled to support the Gallican position, an alphabetical subject index, and the privilege of the University of Paris.

supportDesc.extent: 328 leaves : 385 x 255 (276 x 140) mm. bound to 390 x 275 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 655, i; page numbers in ink contemporary with the brief works (p. 555-654), upper outer corners.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 13-16 long lines, side margins ruled in drypoint (first work); the later works have more than twice as many lines per page, with the same side margins but irregularly narrower top and bottom margins.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: First work in one hand (p. 1-553); remaining works in one smaller hand (p. 555-654).

origin.p: Written in France, the first work after 1718 and the remaining works after 1731.
